def: Of a yellowish or redish brown color; as, a sorrel horse.
Quality or state of being recluse.
Grown old. Hence: Bygone; obsolete; out of use; old-fashioned;as, an antiquated law. "Antiquated words." Dryden.Old Janet, for so he understood his antiquated attendant wasdenominated. Sir W. Scott.
One of a kind of minute, calcareous bodies, probably vegetable,often abundant in deep-sea mud.
A salt of fluoboric acid; a fluoboride.
To levy certain exactions or tribute upon; to lodge and eat atthe expense of. See Coshering.
